Shape.Name: Process.1001
Shape.Text: Open a web browser and Sign In to the RTAA ArcGIS Online Organization

Shape.Name: Process.1002
Shape.Text: Click on the Content Tab

Shape.Name: Process.1003
Shape.Text: On the left, in the Folders section, click on the folder that contains the layer being collected. The folders are organized by feature dataset from the master Geodatabase.

Shape.Name: Process.1004
Shape.Text:
Select the name of the layer being collected. This will open the Item Details page
*Hint – Layers with “New” in front of their name are Views and should not be exported

Shape.Name: Process.1005
Shape.Text: On the right, expand the Export Data dropdown and choose ‘Export to FGDB’

Shape.Name: Process.1006
Shape.Text:
Copy the Title text and paste it into the Tags and Summary fields. Leave the ‘Save in folder’ option as the default which will be the folder containing the layer you are exporting.
Click Export.

Shape.Name: Process.1007
Shape.Text: After a minute or two, the Item Details for the File Geodatabase will be displayed. On the right, click the Download button.

Shape.Name: Process.1008
Shape.Text: Copy the downloaded zip file to a folder accessible in your Pro Project. Extract the zip file.
